title: Malacosoma americanum, Tent-caterpillar Moth Larva
description: This is the larva of the Tent-caterpillar moth photographed on the bark of Quercus palustris, a Pin oak tree. The animal's head is on the left. Please see en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tent_caterpillar for more information on this destructive pest.It is best not to handle tent caterpillars with one's bare hands because their fine hairs (cilia) contain skin irritants which may cause dermatitis in some people.The pale gray-green lichen on the tree bark is Flavoparmelia caperata.Photograph by David Illig and Gerry Doyle.Photographed at Gambrills, Anne Arundel County, Maryland, on May 17, 2014.
